Source: mail, The major objective of scientific endeavour

We've collected few hints that help you to differ scientific research from pseudoscientific. Nowadays there are many 
research that look like scientific, but they are not. As conclusion common person and sometimes researchers may 
mistakenly use incorrect sources for their statements. So new easy to use tool for differentiation is needed to be developed. 
Different aspects of research work like data gathering methods or measurement techniques was compared between scientific 
and pseudoscientific publications, and corresponded characteristics was collected. By using this checklist everyone can 
identify some of pseudoscientific works and minimize wasted time.